Peru Stocks: Candente, Cerro Verde, Relapasa, Southern Copper

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-07T22:35:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/peru-stocks-candente-cerro-verde-relapasa-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 0.4 percent to 22,563.34. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 0.5 percent to 3,078.58.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, rose 1.4 percent to 2.14 soles, the highest
closing price since January 2010, after crude climbed to a 29-
month high in New York.    Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, advanced 1.3 percent to $2.43 after Chief Operating
Officer Alex Black said the company plans to start producing
gold at its La Arena mine next month.  Copper and zinc miners declined after the metals slumped in
New York and  London .    Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, fell 2.8 percent to $2.09.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, dropped 2.7 percent to $41.
Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., slid 1 percent to $48. Cia.
Minera Milpo (MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and lead producer controlled
by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., fell 1.4 percent to
7.05 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  